 stop anything. It's really more of a debug print. And so in this particular example,

00:11:20.240 --> 00:11:26.400
 it just runs. It doesn't stop. The alert stops everything. And so I use the alert like,

00:11:26.400 --> 00:11:31.440
 what is going on? But if I'm really debugging something like in a loop, I'll use console.log.

